summary:
I'm not in it for short term benefit. I'm here for the long haul.

Experienced in the field of sustainable transportation and dedicated to delivering solutions for cities that seek greater environmental, social and economical sustainability.

I have 15 years experience in running projects, starting local initiatives, supporting programs, preparing publications or delivering workshops and speaking engagements.

My expertise is closely linked to my passion: how to make cities work better, how to support community resilience, how to get more people on bicycles, how to create beautiful and functional public space, how to bring both an ecological and human dimension to planning.

I have lived in eight different countries and speak nearly as many languages. I believe in the "glocal" (global-local) approach and find that a multi-cultural perspective and a "can do" attitude is the best way to engage in meaningful work.
